      "message": "The comment about them existing during build creation is only on infra and input.properties, but you mean it applies to all of these? If they are trimmed before writing to datastore then they never exist in the proto when the proto is in the datastore, right? I guess I don\u0027t understand the reason the comment is written this way:\nhttps://chromium.googlesource.com/infra/infra/+/c5050e19726f7dedd73b9af78468afda665e55cd/appengine/cr-buildbucket/model.py#126\n\n1. \"does exist during build creation, and moved into BuildInputProperties right before initial datastore.put\". In other words, never exists in the proto in the datastore. In which case I wouldn\u0027t bother to include the \"CAVEAT\". Can I just say it\u0027s not in the proto in the datastore?\n\n2. The caveat is only written for 2/5 of these so I thought it implied there is some difference.",
